## Comments

### Principles

1. **Explain WHY, Not WHAT** — Code shows what, comments explain why
2. **Don't Comment Obvious Things** — Code should be self-explanatory
3. **Delete Old Comments** — Outdated comments mislead
4. **Delete Commented Code** — Use version control

### Examples

```java
// ❌ BAD - Comments explain obvious code
// Loop through customers
for (Customer c : customers) {
  // Check if active
  if (c.isActive()) {
    // Add to list
    result.add(c);
  }
}

// ✅ GOOD - Comment explains non-obvious reason
// Premium customers get priority even during peak load
for (Customer c : customers) {
  if (c.isActive() && c.isPremium()) {
    result.add(0, c);  // Prepend for priority
  }
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - Self-explanatory code doesn't need comment
// Get the sum of all prices
const total = items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);

// ✅ GOOD - Comment explains business rule
// Prices include tax, but we need base price for external reporting
const baseTotal = items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.basePrice, 0);
```

