## Formatting

### Vertical Density

Related code should be close; unrelated code should be separated.

```java
// ❌ BAD - Whitespace where it shouldn't be
class Parser {
  private String input;
  
  public void parse() {
    // ...
  }
  
  private String input;  // Whitespace breaks association
}
```

```java
// ✅ GOOD - Related code grouped
class Parser {
  private String input;
  private int position;
  private int length;
  
  public void parse() { /* ... */ }
  public String tokenize() { /* ... */ }
  public Node buildTree() { /* ... */ }
}
```

### Method Ordering

1. Static factories and constructors
2. Public methods (most important first)
3. Private methods (least important last)

```java
class Order {
  // Factory
  public static Order create() { /* ... */ }
  
  // Public methods - most important first
  public void place() { /* ... */ }
  public void cancel() { /* ... */ }
  public Money total() { /* ... */ }
  
  // Private helpers - least important
  private void validateCanPlace() { /* ... */ }
  private void calculateLines() { /* ... */ }
}
```

### Horizontal Spacing

```java
// ❌ BAD - Inconsistent
int x=a+b*c;
String s = "hello";
function foo( int a,int b){}

// ✅ GOOD - Consistent spacing
int x = a + b * c;
String s = "hello";
function foo(int a, int b) {}
```

